social_posts.post_text: Hunters AE86. I bought this this almost 10 years ago and it was a present for him (us) so I can make a version of his favorite anime Initial D. I was thinking of repainting it to its original silver color but still 50-50 on that. Just 3 more years and he will be driving it on the streets!

December Storytime is live now. Check the link in my bio to watch/listen!

Mark Arcenal @mrk.rcnl hails from the Bay Area in California. He is an artist and a trailblazer in fashion and car culture. He is a major reason for what is widely known today as "stanced cars".

We talk about his love for both industries and how they influenced his journey to create his website Fatlace and Illest brand. He is an inspirational person to many and this interview will show you why.

For this episode of Storytime, Mark takes us through his ambitious plan to hold a Hellaflush event in the place that inspired his love for his drifting style of cars - Japan. His Hellaflush event at Fuji Speedway was huge and he filled the event with 400+ cars with street cars, drift cars, D1 cars and even the Cyber Evo. 

#drifting #driftinghistory #fatlace #hellaflush #stance #stancenation #podcasts #driftingpodcast

Thank you Ken for always being you. Every time you emailed 928374 times before getting on the phone to get settled on the concept, and before we even got to discuss work, family came first. We talked about how our kids were doing, and what kind of races both of us were looking forward to, and never once did we not talk about how much we both missed Japan. I’m going to miss you dude. Rest in Paradise. Prayers to the entire Block Family & everyone mourning his loss. 

Thanks to everyone who reached out with hundreds of messages. Sorry, I didn’t get back to you as I was on the road. I appreciate you all. #kb43ver
G / G #leica
Thunderhill, see you soon.

Two Car Solution. My friend Takeshi put on a private underground event last night. Was supposed to be private but turned out not so much. Anyways, here’s the two car solution post. The Evo 1 & 2 takes the cake but I do love the pairing of the FDs. Something about yellow and dark grey metallic works well.

Meanwhile back in the states… Danny from RMC helped me secure this slick top 34k miles Midnight Blue on Viola Blue interior. Been a long 3 month wait but stoked to see its almost home. This is part of my Navy & Silver collection. Came with a light flywheel, turbo brakes and an awesome purplish blue interior. Hit me up if you want an intro. Good dudes.
RAUH-Welt Begriff HQ 2023

Was wondering when I’d get back into a 964 after being tempted with quite a few gems from the boys at RMC Miami. This one, however, I couldn’t pass up. Found this 1990 Navy Slick Top with Viola Blue interior with only 40k miles in Japan. Came with a ton of RS parts, turbo brakes, lightened flywheel and more. Thanks again Danny for helping secure this one. Now to get it all sorted out with proper suspension and wheels.
The japan-specd viola blue interior really pops in the sun.

Took a trip to Tokyo with a few friends. Didn’t have much of an agenda as I was just stoked on visiting one of my favorite places on earth.

Carlin says to me last week, “you need to get a dip stick for the AE86”… most of you car guys know it’s never just one part so Hunters 86 is finally getting its shine. Looking forward to the debut of the 2 piece forged line by Motegi Racing. Thanks to @bcracingna @battlegarage_rs and of course @ipautodesign for setting this thing up.

Camp vibes at Thunderhill in Cindys Taycan. Got to use the baseball heater for a little bit. This 5000lbs Porsche felt extremely heavy on the turns but definitely planted. Took a while for me to find the breaking point being awd. The 19k mile old tires let me know when it was ready to go though! Time to change them out!
@mrk.rcnl brought his AE86 to the track on a new set of @motegiracing wheels, It went well… 😮‍💨
Stoked to see the sun finally out. Slapped these Kinesis Supercups on for the upcoming Luftgekult show. Hope to see you there.

The 65 Nova project just completed its custom interior, paint and is now at the shop back in norcal getting a well deserved engine refresh. I never had intentions of spending so much on it but I’m thankful it’s almost nearing completion. Redoing the front suspension is next and then it should finally be ready for the 49ers season opener. Btw, if you never had Ai Pono, you haven’t lived yet. Thee best Hawaiian in SoCal.
The standard driveway shot. This time with the 38k mile slicktop ROW 964. Featuring some amazing Kinesis Supercups which btw are available now on Kinesismotorsport.com

Had a good dinner at the Elkhorn Lodge tonight. Saw this beautiful 997RS which reminded me of Jeff @zwart old 4.0. Ate the Seafood Combo and the other mark had a gigantic double burger! Thunderhill tomorrow.

Had a well deserved two days at Thunderhill East. Spent lots of time understanding where I could improve as well as talking #dadlife with a few dads. Stoked to see a bunch of friends and looking forward to the next one.

Last Sunday… #gt3rs #porsche
Tracklife & Vanlife

Had a great time with Brooklyn at the tail end of Car Week 2023. It’s our annual father daughter weekend and it’s a bittersweet one as she heads to college this week. Didn’t get to take too many photos but it was great to catch up with a bunch of you.

The road to consistent low 1:30s at Laguna Seca is practice. It’s usually this foggy in the mornings when you get here this time of year. I’ve been building this 2015 991 GT3 for a few months now. It’s equipped with PMNA rear cup car aero and front aero fenders, soon to be full cup suspension and everything in between. Stoked about the setup for now and really happy it can challenge all the new GT cars out there. Removed the headers and full exhaust to keep this thing as quiet as possible on track. A little sneak peak of the livery it’ll have at the next event.

The simplest things in life are the most satisfying. Drilled thru the oem gt3 bumper to install the factory gt3 cup rain/brake light (brake, in my case) at Carlins shop today. This cleared the factory 3rd brake light reminder on the dash. Hoping to clear more of the lights on the dash before Laguna Seca. #porsche #gt3cup
The old team. 2016.

Just the little adjustments makes the biggest differences. A completely stock GT3 with suspension and cup car aero can keep up with all the latest technology. Thanks to everyone that helped set this car up and my track friends that keep me pushing. Looking forward to the next one. #porschegt3 #porsche #lagunaseca #RoadTo129
If you haven’t driven Laguna, you haven’t driven! The new surface just keeps getting better. Can’t wait to add a few more tweaks to the suspension and go back soon. #porsche #gt3 #RoadTo129

It’s been a few years since I’ve been back to Portland. Yesterday’s weather was fantastic and I’m looking forward to seeing friends today.

Fun little fact: I lived in this Hotel when I started working at Nike in 2006. If you know my journey, you know many things have happened since then, but working here inspired a younger me to be even more motivated today.
New album cover shot. #893

It’s been about 9 years since I actually took a car out to drift. Thanks to everyone that made this day happen and sorry it’s not super fast style since it wasn’t my car. Forgot how much fun it is and how therapeutic it is. Thanks Audel & Arianne for letting me drive your cars and Raymond for letting us, the illest manila team, use the track. Hopefully I can build a drift car in manila to keep doing it. #DriftUnit

At the conclusion of my 2023 track days, I consistently achieved lap times of 1:31 at Laguna Seca (check out a lap by swiping). Despite my 2015 GT3 having 55k miles on it, it performed impressively. I made no engine modifications other than adding a PMNA Carrera Cup Intake. Instead, I concentrated on enhancing the car's aerodynamics, suspension, and fitting the widest wheel and tire combination possible. My goal for next year is to achieve 1:29s! #991streetcup ( full video https://youtu.be/U-SvfC91i6M?si )
